WEBVTT

1
00:00:26.500 --> 00:00:30.270

<font face="微软雅黑" size="30">DELTA DEL EBRO</font>

2
00:01:59.960 --> 00:02:01.260
Is that all?

3
00:02:01.440 --> 00:02:02.420
Yeah. yeah. that's it.

4
00:02:02.680 --> 00:02:03.570
Ninety cents. please.

5
00:02:06.930 --> 00:02:07.840
Sounds good.

6
00:02:08.520 --> 00:02:09.540
Keep the change. ma'am.

7
00:02:11.020 --> 00:02:12.040
Thanks a lot.

8
00:02:13.100 --> 00:02:15.070
Just wait for a second while I get the car. alright?

9
00:02:15.200 --> 00:02:16.060
Hurry.

10
00:02:20.780 --> 00:02:21.860
What a freak.

11
00:02:30.300 --> 00:02:32.000
What the fuck happened?

12
00:02:36.570 --> 00:02:38.690
Stop! Stop it!

13
00:02:39.600 --> 00:02:40.780
How did you do that?

14
00:02:40.970 --> 00:02:42.230
Get out! Get out!

15
00:02:42.370 --> 00:02:43.220
Fuck!

16
00:02:45.850 --> 00:02:47.020
Just drop the hammer.

17
00:02:51.690 --> 00:02:53.650
What are you gonna do. little boy?

18
00:02:56.340 --> 00:02:57.710
Pls don't make me do it.

19
00:03:00.200 --> 00:03:01.200
Stay back now!

20
00:03:04.440 --> 00:03:06.020
Don't come any closer!

21
00:03:17.590 --> 00:03:18.480
Ian!

22
00:03:27.830 --> 00:03:29.410
Oh. what have you done.

23
00:03:29.460 --> 00:03:31.100
Let's go. You screwed up. Come on.

24
00:03:34.060 --> 00:03:35.100
Help me!

25
00:03:37.230 --> 00:03:38.370
Help me!

26
00:03:38.720 --> 00:03:40.350
Easy. ma'am. Ma'am. what's wrong? Calm down.

27
00:03:40.410 --> 00:03:41.910
- I've been shot. - Where?

28
00:03:41.930 --> 00:03:43.070
They shot me!

29
00:03:43.370 --> 00:03:45.510
You're not hurt. ma'am. You weren't hit. Relax.

30
00:03:47.440 --> 00:03:48.330
What?

31
00:03:49.070 --> 00:03:50.150
I've been robbed!

32
00:03:59.880 --> 00:04:01.210
Oh. goddanm it. the car.

33
00:04:01.450 --> 00:04:02.910
This is the third one this year.

34
00:04:03.000 --> 00:04:03.770
It's stolen.

35
00:04:03.830 --> 00:04:05.050
But I actually like this one.

36
00:04:05.240 --> 00:04:08.040
Son. do what you need to do. Just don't let them see this car.

37
00:04:23.540 --> 00:04:25.120
Why the fuck did you do that?

38
00:04:25.580 --> 00:04:28.280
Don't you remember the rules? We only have two rules. Got that?

39
00:04:28.530 --> 00:04:30.300
The first is don't call attention to yourself.

40
00:04:30.340 --> 00:04:32.560
Yeah. and the second rule is you can't play tricks on your family.

41
00:04:32.700 --> 00:04:33.600
Okay?

42
00:04:42.440 --> 00:04:45.300
Why do we always have to settle for these stupid little crumbs?

43
00:04:45.940 --> 00:04:47.820
What if we could do one big hit and live the life?

44
00:04:47.920 --> 00:04:49.540
Don't start with that again. Come on.

45
00:04:59.070 --> 00:05:03.830
I just walk into a bank. make them think I have a check. and boom. boom. I got all the dough.

46
00:05:03.890 --> 00:05:07.970
I told you a thousand times. no. Banks are the Champions League. and we play in the third division.

47
00:05:08.520 --> 00:05:11.020
Plus. they would find us before you could spend your first euro.

48
00:05:11.130 --> 00:05:12.900
They'd find us? Who?

49
00:05:13.770 --> 00:05:17.170
Let me be very clear. If they catch you. they'll take you to a laboratory.

50
00:05:17.240 --> 00:05:18.340
Get that through your head.

51
00:05:18.560 --> 00:05:21.190
They won't ask permission. and they'll run hundreds of tests on you.

52
00:05:21.310 --> 00:05:24.670
That's why we have rules. Follow them. and we can live in peace.

53
00:05:31.960 --> 00:05:34.680
Code 10- 43. alleged aggravated robbery.

54
00:05:35.120 --> 00:05:38.660
Suspect in Alansia Delta. headed south on local road 2- 12.

55
00:05:40.140 --> 00:05:44.860
Stop the vehicle immediately! I repeat. stop the vehicle immediately!

56
00:05:49.160 --> 00:05:52.120
Wait a second. Hold on. What are you doing?

57
00:05:52.250 --> 00:05:53.930
Stop the vehicle immediately!

58
00:05:54.100 --> 00:05:56.560
Ian. you don't have as much control as you think you have!

59
00:05:58.200 --> 00:05:59.720
Stop the car immediately!

60
00:07:01.010 --> 00:07:02.610
You want to fill it up?

61
00:07:06.720 --> 00:07:11.260
Yes. I'm looking at them. Good job.

62
00:07:12.770 --> 00:07:15.750
Turn around. Get the helicopter ready.

63
00:07:20.560 --> 00:07:21.560
Finally

64
00:07:25.650 --> 00:07:32.310

<font face="微软雅黑" size="30">AWARENESS  
 Dex7er:yelang5460@126.com</font>

65
00:07:39.940 --> 00:07:45.280
Paca. Oh. my Paca. There you are.

66
00:07:48.160 --> 00:07:49.020
Here.

67
00:07:49.990 --> 00:07:55.490
Singing. don't worry about a thing.

68
00:07:56.660 --> 00:08:01.080
Because every little thing is gonna be alright.

69
00:08:09.610 --> 00:08:14.130
Happy birthday to you

70
00:08:15.500 --> 00:08:18.600
Happy birthday

71
00:08:18.870 --> 00:08:21.240
Okay. okay. Dad. I got it.

72
00:08:22.250 --> 00:08:24.130
Stop singing. My head hurts.

73
00:08:24.150 --> 00:08:29.270
Happy birthday from your father.

74
00:08:29.830 --> 00:08:34.390
Happy birthday to you.

75
00:08:38.870 --> 00:08:40.470
Come on. Make a wish.

76
00:08:40.500 --> 00:08:41.590
Okay.

77
00:08:44.510 --> 00:08:45.550
Good.

78
00:08:47.440 --> 00:08:48.700
Thanks. Dad.

79
00:08:50.630 --> 00:08:55.990
I thought about this all night. I've got a plan.

80
00:08:57.750 --> 00:09:00.270
I'm going to find a job as a mechanic.

81
00:09:00.750 --> 00:09:03.350
That way you can focus on getting your biology degree.

82
00:09:03.550 --> 00:09:06.310
which shouldn't take too long with that big brain of yours.

83
00:09:06.670 --> 00:09:08.680
Then we can finally live.

84
00:09:11.870 --> 00:09:13.990
You've already lost your mother. and

85
00:09:15.070 --> 00:09:17.310
I don't want to lose you. too.

86
00:09:17.940 --> 00:09:21.030
Oh. and you know what else kept me up thinking all night?

87
00:09:21.430 --> 00:09:23.050
Look. Look at her.

88
00:09:24.400 --> 00:09:25.720
Look how pretty she was.

89
00:09:28.300 --> 00:09:33.400
That day. you realized you could do all those things you do.

90
00:09:34.000 --> 00:09:36.460
As you already know. you had two obsessions as a kid.

91
00:09:36.580 --> 00:09:38.560
Those animal crackers. those cookies and balloons.

92
00:09:38.680 --> 00:09:40.800
I want a balloon. I want a balloon.

93
00:09:41.260 --> 00:09:45.240
You were always fussing. asking that we buy you more balloons.

94
00:09:45.760 --> 00:09:48.520
And that day. I don't know. you were probably fed up.

95
00:09:50.900 --> 00:09:53.300
So you just decided to make them yourself.

96
00:09:54.060 --> 00:09:56.120
I still don't know what exactly happened.

97
00:09:56.750 --> 00:10:01.070
and all of a sudden. you made them all pop at once.

98
00:10:02.410 --> 00:10:03.720
I'm off.

99
00:10:05.470 --> 00:10:07.720
No. Where are you going? Come here.

100
00:10:08.460 --> 00:10:10.520
I told you yesterday. I have plans.

101
00:10:10.540 --> 00:10:12.260
Yeah. but it's not a good idea.

102
00:10:12.580 --> 00:10:16.140
I've been living on this boat for years. With your rules.

103
00:10:17.450 --> 00:10:18.450
Listen.

104
00:10:20.240 --> 00:10:22.520
I'm just going to the arcade for a little while.

105
00:10:23.780 --> 00:10:27.110
It's so dangerous to do something normal. Just this once.

106
00:10:27.280 --> 00:10:30.390
- please. come on  - But that's it. No. You are not normal.

107
00:10:30.910 --> 00:10:33.770
And especially after the crazy show you put on yesterday.

108
00:10:34.010 --> 00:10:35.650
We had to follow a zero-risk policy.

109
00:10:35.750 --> 00:10:37.690
She was going to bash your head in with a hammer.

110
00:10:37.760 --> 00:10:38.780
You know that. right?

111
00:10:38.820 --> 00:10:40.330
Yes. and I appreciate that. But

112
00:10:40.420 --> 00:10:42.520
Son. please don't worry about me.

113
00:10:44.340 --> 00:10:46.380
You're the only one that matters here.

114
00:10:48.160 --> 00:10:49.460
Doesn't feel like it.

115
00:10:54.560 --> 00:10:56.260
Wait. Hold on a second.

116
00:11:46.160 --> 00:11:49.340
I swear to you. it started to hail heavily.

117
00:11:49.530 --> 00:11:51.610
Seriously? It never. ever hails here.

118
00:11:51.710 --> 00:11:53.250
And that's not the weirdest part.

119
00:11:53.600 --> 00:11:57.260
Since no one believed me. I asked to see the footage from the car and the grocery store.

120
00:11:58.370 --> 00:12:01.470
And I went to the gas station to get their CCTV footage.

121
00:12:01.980 --> 00:12:03.020
And you know what?

122
00:12:03.780 --> 00:12:05.760
They told me it had already been taken.

123
00:12:06.540 --> 00:12:08.820
By your colleagues. they said.

124
00:12:09.430 --> 00:12:11.450
Some guys wearing black jackets.

125
00:12:11.760 --> 00:12:12.780
Fucking bastards.

126
00:12:25.090 --> 00:12:26.300
Oh. shit!

127
00:12:27.330 --> 00:12:28.410
Are you okay?

128
00:13:24.900 --> 00:13:25.960
Ian?

129
00:13:27.490 --> 00:13:29.260
Come here. I am on a Bruce Lee.

130
00:13:36.930 --> 00:13:37.910
Ian!

131
00:13:58.010 --> 00:14:00.410
Thanks for that show you put on for the Civil Guard.

132
00:14:01.150 --> 00:14:03.750
If it wasn't for that. the agency wouldn't have found you.

133
00:14:03.960 --> 00:14:05.130
The agency?

134
00:14:06.100 --> 00:14:09.140
Very official sounding name for a not so official organization.

135
00:14:09.780 --> 00:14:11.750
You still calling them perceivers. or did you...

136
00:14:11.770 --> 00:14:12.760
Perceiver.

137
00:14:13.620 --> 00:14:14.520
Singular.

138
00:14:14.820 --> 00:14:15.990
There's only one.

139
00:14:16.690 --> 00:14:18.990
And trust me. he won't last much longer.

140
00:14:20.220 --> 00:14:21.370
Where's the kid?

141
00:14:22.550 --> 00:14:24.530
I don't give a damn what you do to me. Adriana.

142
00:14:32.290 --> 00:14:34.370
I'm not going to ask you again.

143
00:14:38.320 --> 00:14:40.720
We got him. Three kilometers away.

144
00:14:40.740 --> 00:14:42.660
His van was spotted outside the arcade.

145
00:15:45.660 --> 00:15:47.010
Entering the arcade.

146
00:16:16.460 --> 00:16:17.850
Perceiver in the area.

147
00:16:18.890 --> 00:16:20.100
Perceiver in the area!

148
00:16:20.250 --> 00:16:21.600
I need instructions and backup.

149
00:16:22.080 --> 00:16:23.060
Change in priority.

150
00:16:23.530 --> 00:16:24.790
Capture the Perceiver.

151
00:16:25.590 --> 00:16:28.040
Listen to me. We cannot let him anywhere near the boy.

152
00:16:41.370 --> 00:16:42.580
Target located.

153
00:16:53.810 --> 00:16:56.450
Target now headed for exit. Awaiting instructions.

154
00:16:56.730 --> 00:16:57.830
Get rid of him.

155
00:17:22.910 --> 00:17:24.100
Don't even look at him.

156
00:17:24.180 --> 00:17:26.570
Listen to me. You're not safe here. Come on. let's go.

157
00:18:24.410 --> 00:18:26.170
You've seen what that man can do.

158
00:18:26.840 --> 00:18:29.560
There's more like you. Ian.

159
00:18:30.970 --> 00:18:32.610
Come with me if you want to live.

160
00:19:20.520 --> 00:19:25.140
We don't have all night. kid. the decision is yours.

161
00:19:37.560 --> 00:19:39.130
Dad. Dad!

162
00:19:39.180 --> 00:19:40.260
There. sit.

163
00:19:40.700 --> 00:19:41.500
Dad!

164
00:19:42.060 --> 00:19:43.220
What are you doing?

165
00:19:45.260 --> 00:19:46.220
I'm sorry.

166
00:20:13.420 --> 00:20:15.900
PROCESSING BLOOD SAMPLE

167
00:20:17.450 --> 00:20:18.630
We've got the kid.

168
00:20:18.860 --> 00:20:20.580
Sending over samples for analysis.

169
00:20:50.840 --> 00:20:52.370
Perceiver has blocked the highway.

170
00:20:52.910 --> 00:20:54.810
Don't believe it. Just keep going.

171
00:21:50.490 --> 00:21:52.700
I'm sorry about the helmet. Ian.

172
00:21:53.620 --> 00:21:56.000
I must guarantee the safety of my team.

173
00:21:57.160 --> 00:21:58.110
Dr. Ladman.

174
00:21:58.470 --> 00:22:00.010
But you can call me Adriana.

175
00:22:00.230 --> 00:22:02.000
I don't give a damn who you are.

176
00:22:02.630 --> 00:22:03.770
What am I doing here?

177
00:22:08.460 --> 00:22:09.860
Let's take a look at history.

178
00:22:10.900 --> 00:22:14.200
Don't you feel like the world is getting worse and worse every day?

179
00:22:16.100 --> 00:22:19.660
Each new government and power promises change and hope.

180
00:22:20.740 --> 00:22:23.920
However. they end up doing exactly the same as their predecessors.

181
00:22:24.880 --> 00:22:27.220
They say one thing and then they do the opposite.

182
00:22:28.670 --> 00:22:32.150
Who has power defines the world we live in today.

183
00:22:32.410 --> 00:22:38.070
But real power can't be bought with money. knowledge or technology.

184
00:22:40.160 --> 00:22:43.500
It is having the ability to create a lie and remain invisible.

185
00:22:45.090 --> 00:22:47.530
To make others believe what you want them to.

186
00:22:49.000 --> 00:22:52.540
And ultimately. if that doesn't lead to concrete action.

187
00:22:53.340 --> 00:22:55.760
To force them to do it against their will.

188
00:22:56.470 --> 00:22:59.210
That way they can redirect the course of history.

189
00:23:00.370 --> 00:23:01.850
That's where the power is.

190
00:23:06.530 --> 00:23:07.950
We're at war. Ian.

191
00:23:09.110 --> 00:23:10.560
Against the awareness.

192
00:23:10.960 --> 00:23:12.370
I don't know what that is.

193
00:23:12.580 --> 00:23:15.480
An organization of people with powers just like yours.

194
00:23:17.920 --> 00:23:20.960
They've controlled the spheres of power for many years now.

195
00:23:21.980 --> 00:23:24.720
Manipulating the minds and decisions of those in power.

196
00:23:25.970 --> 00:23:28.390
Rulers and politicians and the military.

197
00:23:29.030 --> 00:23:31.150
That's why it doesn't matter who governs.

198
00:23:31.770 --> 00:23:34.610
In the end. they'll follow the path set by the awareness.

199
00:23:35.670 --> 00:23:37.190
We're here to stop that.

200
00:23:37.940 --> 00:23:40.980
And to preserve the little democracy that is left in the world.

201
00:23:42.570 --> 00:23:44.170
What does that have to do with me?

202
00:23:44.920 --> 00:23:47.820
Well. you're still alive because we got to you before he did.

203
00:23:49.120 --> 00:23:50.220
Who was he?

204
00:23:52.280 --> 00:23:53.460
That man.

205
00:23:54.190 --> 00:23:55.310
He is a perceiver.

206
00:23:58.570 --> 00:23:59.410
A what?

207
00:23:59.690 --> 00:24:00.930
A perceiver.

208
00:24:01.970 --> 00:24:04.850
We believe he's the last remaining member of the awareness.

209
00:24:05.430 --> 00:24:07.500
He can create projections like you.

210
00:24:07.930 --> 00:24:09.440
As well as many other things.

211
00:24:10.390 --> 00:24:12.530
He's the most powerful one we've ever faced.

212
00:24:13.380 --> 00:24:14.830
He wants you to join him.

213
00:24:15.440 --> 00:24:17.800
If you don't. he'll kill you.

214
00:24:19.830 --> 00:24:20.680
Great.

215
00:24:21.060 --> 00:24:22.030
Kill me.

216
00:24:26.340 --> 00:24:27.680
What do you want?

217
00:24:34.480 --> 00:24:36.560
I want you to work with me. Ian.

218
00:24:39.220 --> 00:24:42.000
And also. I want the formula in your blood.

219
00:24:43.480 --> 00:24:44.660
What formula?

220
00:24:45.180 --> 00:24:48.420
The one that can create or deactivate your powers.

221
00:24:49.760 --> 00:24:51.400
What else can you project?

222
00:24:53.090 --> 00:24:54.620
Bigger objects?

223
00:24:56.280 --> 00:24:57.160
Surroundings?

224
00:24:58.380 --> 00:24:59.380
People?

225
00:25:01.380 --> 00:25:03.560
I've tried that many times. but it can't be done.

226
00:25:04.640 --> 00:25:05.600
Yes. it can.

227
00:25:06.130 --> 00:25:07.590
Alright. tell me where my father is.

228
00:25:07.810 --> 00:25:09.290
I mean you no harm. Ian.

229
00:25:09.880 --> 00:25:11.140
Then tell me where he is.

230
00:25:11.160 --> 00:25:11.970
All in due time.

231
00:25:11.990 --> 00:25:13.070
Just tell me where he is!

232
00:25:13.070 --> 00:25:14.070
I just want to help you.

233
00:25:14.090 --> 00:25:15.110
What happened to my father?

234
00:25:15.140 --> 00:25:16.010
Calm down.

235
00:25:23.160 --> 00:25:25.920
First do something for me. then you can see your father.

236
00:25:27.270 --> 00:25:28.500
Let's see where you're at.

237
00:25:29.230 --> 00:25:32.790
I want you to make me think that it's a nice day at the beach.

238
00:25:34.040 --> 00:25:35.240
Lots of sun.

239
00:25:36.460 --> 00:25:37.920
Pretty white sand.

240
00:25:38.820 --> 00:25:42.180
Drinking a mojito with a chihuahua at my side.

241
00:25:48.070 --> 00:25:49.310
Hey look. doctor.

242
00:25:49.530 --> 00:25:50.810
That's not how this works.

243
00:25:51.810 --> 00:25:56.550
I might be able to make you see something. but not as spectacular as that.

244
00:25:56.700 --> 00:25:58.000
Don't be afraid.

245
00:25:58.220 --> 00:26:00.020
You're able to run before you can walk.

246
00:26:01.290 --> 00:26:04.920
Emotions are a great catalyst for your powers.

247
00:26:05.730 --> 00:26:09.250
The more intense the emotion. the greater your ability to project.

248
00:26:10.280 --> 00:26:13.880
Find a strong emotion and project it onto me.

249
00:26:14.910 --> 00:26:16.580
Search inside yourself.

250
00:26:17.990 --> 00:26:20.710
I'm pretty sure your childhood wasn't easy. right?

251
00:26:21.810 --> 00:26:23.020
What do you know?

252
00:26:23.450 --> 00:26:25.560
I've been looking for you for years.

253
00:26:26.410 --> 00:26:29.390
But Vicente managed to keep you completely hidden.

254
00:26:30.650 --> 00:26:33.320
I imagine by moving you from town to town.

255
00:26:34.200 --> 00:26:37.270
no school. no friends.

256
00:26:43.600 --> 00:26:45.090
And no mother.

257
00:27:12.290 --> 00:27:14.150
And now the chihuahua.

258
00:27:23.340 --> 00:27:26.280
A horsefly? Really?

259
00:27:27.160 --> 00:27:31.320
So now I want to go home and keep this horsefly on a loop.

260
00:27:32.460 --> 00:27:34.760
It's a projection. but it lasts forever.

261
00:27:35.040 --> 00:27:37.530
The subject doesn't even know that it's not real.

262
00:27:37.950 --> 00:27:40.640
Like a sick man who sees things no one else can see.

263
00:27:41.080 --> 00:27:43.840
This loop will always be a part of my reality.

264
00:27:58.220 --> 00:27:59.980
Your free trial is now over.

265
00:28:02.430 --> 00:28:05.650
If you want more. take me to my father.

266
