00:54:18.180 --> 00:54:21.020
And you forced me to live your fucking miserable life!

545
00:54:22.630 --> 00:54:24.910
You've turned me into a miserable guy.

546
00:54:25.850 --> 00:54:26.930
Just like you.

547
00:54:32.510 --> 00:54:33.570
The balloons?

548
00:54:39.310 --> 00:54:41.610
What the fuck was all that about the balloons?

549
00:54:43.870 --> 00:54:44.950
Was it fun?

550
00:54:45.230 --> 00:54:46.460
Making up all that shit?

551
00:54:46.600 --> 00:54:48.540
Everything I've done. I've done for you.

552
00:54:49.160 --> 00:54:51.080
It's not hard to understand.

553
00:54:51.280 --> 00:54:53.110
If you break any of the rules...

554
00:54:53.160 --> 00:54:54.670
What rules? What rules?

555
00:54:56.630 --> 00:54:58.770
Not playing tricks on family?

556
00:54:58.820 --> 00:54:59.340
No.

557
00:54:59.400 --> 00:55:02.180
No? Because it turns out you're not my father!

558
00:55:02.200 --> 00:55:03.540
No. let's calm down.

559
00:55:03.980 --> 00:55:07.460
Keeping you away from the world was the only thing I could think of to protect you.

560
00:55:07.540 --> 00:55:09.360
I know I haven't been the perfect father...

561
00:55:09.400 --> 00:55:11.020
You're not my fucking father!

562
00:55:19.360 --> 00:55:20.140
You're right.

563
00:55:21.480 --> 00:55:22.700
I'm not your father.

564
00:55:25.960 --> 00:55:27.580
But you are my son.

565
00:55:33.900 --> 00:55:35.840
Listen carefully. because...

566
00:55:37.120 --> 00:55:39.040
I'm only going to say this once. Ian.

567
00:55:42.740 --> 00:55:44.140
You have two options.

568
00:55:45.700 --> 00:55:47.800
You can keep going down this road you're on.

569
00:55:47.820 --> 00:55:50.740
which I guarantee will bring you nothing but pain...

570
00:55:51.100 --> 00:55:52.170
and suffering.

571
00:55:52.860 --> 00:55:54.260
Or you can come with me.

572
00:55:56.620 --> 00:55:59.340
And then we can start all over again.

573
00:55:59.360 --> 00:56:00.290
You and me.

574
00:56:00.550 --> 00:56:01.570
Just us.

575
00:56:02.570 --> 00:56:04.650
Together. like it used to be. you know?

576
00:56:26.280 --> 00:56:27.500
He's getting too confident.

577
00:56:27.710 --> 00:56:28.760
What else have we got?

578
00:56:29.470 --> 00:56:31.710
We have the serial numbers from the stolen cash.

579
00:56:31.790 --> 00:56:33.560
We're already tracking any purchases.

580
00:56:37.110 --> 00:56:37.820
Speak.

581
00:56:38.170 --> 00:56:40.410
We got him. Doctor. He just bought train tickets.

582
00:56:41.110 --> 00:56:42.320
Activate the protocol.

583
00:56:48.640 --> 00:56:49.860
He's trying to disappear.

584
00:56:50.630 --> 00:56:51.630
No. he's not.

585
00:56:52.400 --> 00:56:53.560
He wants answers.

586
00:57:02.950 --> 00:57:05.910
VARSOVIA

587
00:57:22.630 --> 00:57:23.510
Sounds good.

588
00:57:26.260 --> 00:57:27.160
Kaminsky?

589
00:57:29.640 --> 00:57:31.600
But I already anticipated the move.

590
00:57:32.650 --> 00:57:34.050
I've got eyes on the ground.

591
00:57:34.160 --> 00:57:35.040
You may be right.

592
00:57:36.260 --> 00:57:39.180
But he could gain access to the third power. That's too dangerous.

593
00:57:40.480 --> 00:57:42.100
He must be eliminated immediately.

594
00:57:46.390 --> 00:57:48.150
Affirmative. They arrived

595
00:58:04.330 --> 00:58:06.270
Looks like no one lives here.

596
00:58:06.740 --> 00:58:08.000
Then why are you whispering?

597
00:58:08.490 --> 00:58:09.410
I don't know.

598
00:58:46.930 --> 00:58:48.130
There's nothing here.

599
00:58:49.370 --> 00:58:50.350
And no one.

600
00:58:58.860 --> 00:59:00.620
Looks like we're back to square one.

601
00:59:01.850 --> 00:59:02.970
At ground zero.

602
00:59:04.330 --> 00:59:05.100
What?

603
00:59:07.810 --> 00:59:10.210
At ground zero. Sounds cooler.

604
00:59:15.910 --> 00:59:17.750
This is the room from my dreams.

605
00:59:21.400 --> 00:59:23.540
I spent hours here. playing with my mom.

606
00:59:25.660 --> 00:59:28.060
I remember a little bunny that...

607
00:59:31.500 --> 00:59:33.000
It's smaller than I remember.

608
00:59:34.830 --> 00:59:36.970
You can't have memories from that age. Ian.

609
00:59:38.010 --> 00:59:39.060
Something's off.

610
00:59:40.340 --> 00:59:44.320
What's off is that the room from my dreams was a lot bigger than this one.

611
00:59:47.240 --> 00:59:49.320
Ian. memory doesn't work the way you think.

612
00:59:51.620 --> 00:59:53.660
You can recall a memory from an image.

613
00:59:53.850 --> 00:59:55.510
But when you were young...

614
00:59:56.000 --> 00:59:57.260
How old were you?

615
00:59:57.330 --> 00:59:58.640
Here... one and a half.

616
01:01:00.700 --> 01:01:01.930
It's her diaries

617
01:01:10.350 --> 01:01:11.420
That's her.

618
01:01:14.970 --> 01:01:16.570
The dream is always the same.

619
01:01:17.970 --> 01:01:19.620
Sitting in that white room.

620
01:01:22.510 --> 01:01:24.790
And she's singing every time.

621
01:01:42.360 --> 01:01:44.130
Her name is Ursula.

622
01:01:44.710 --> 01:01:46.750
Ursula Kaminsky.

623
01:01:49.370 --> 01:01:51.030
You're Kaminsky's grandson.

624
01:02:41.580 --> 01:02:43.220
Drinking won't help you forget.

625
01:02:44.270 --> 01:02:45.970
Is that your solution to everything?

626
01:02:48.880 --> 01:02:51.760
You weren't so nice last time. What do you want?

627
01:02:52.070 --> 01:02:54.110
We know that Ian is on his own now.

628
01:02:55.120 --> 01:02:56.750
He's very easy to track.

629
01:02:58.160 --> 01:03:00.480
If we can find him that easily...

630
01:03:02.130 --> 01:03:03.710
The perceiver can too.

631
01:03:04.000 --> 01:03:06.120
If you really wanted to help him. you could...

632
01:03:07.370 --> 01:03:08.870
just leave him alone now.

633
01:03:09.010 --> 01:03:10.050
It's not that easy.

634
01:03:11.810 --> 01:03:14.430
Ian is the only person who can go against the Mule.

635
01:03:14.710 --> 01:03:16.500
He's our only hope. and you know that.

636
01:03:16.530 --> 01:03:18.630
Look at yourself. Adriana.

637
01:03:19.830 --> 01:03:23.230
All these years later. and you're still going on about the Mule.

638
01:03:25.260 --> 01:03:26.700
No man's lands.

639
01:03:27.020 --> 01:03:28.300
That was my choice.

640
01:03:28.770 --> 01:03:30.310
The awareness on one side.

641
01:03:31.000 --> 01:03:32.490
the agency on the other.

642
01:03:32.570 --> 01:03:34.080
And the kid and me in the middle.

643
01:03:36.640 --> 01:03:38.580
Not choosing one side or the other.

644
01:03:39.640 --> 01:03:42.000
He's decided to follow his own path.

645
01:03:44.230 --> 01:03:46.230
I have to learn to respect that.

646
01:03:46.540 --> 01:03:48.670
Ian is outside of our protection now.

647
01:03:49.820 --> 01:03:52.820
He's alone. lost. and he can be easily manipulated.

648
01:03:53.620 --> 01:03:55.860
And in the meantime. you're not choosing sides?

649
01:04:10.710 --> 01:04:12.490
You should really give up drinking.

650
01:04:12.540 --> 01:04:15.740
and for once in your life. dare to finally be a real father to him.

651
01:04:23.740 --> 01:04:25.740
I'm sure there's a clue somewhere in here.

652
01:04:31.710 --> 01:04:32.640
Esther?

653
01:04:40.870 --> 01:04:41.790
What is this?

654
01:04:41.890 --> 01:04:42.690
I'm helping you.

655
01:04:43.310 --> 01:04:44.130
Helping me?

656
01:04:44.940 --> 01:04:45.900
What's going on. Esther?

657
01:04:46.030 --> 01:04:47.090
You wanted answers. right?

658
01:04:47.190 --> 01:04:48.450
Then listen to what he has to say.

659
01:04:50.330 --> 01:04:52.150
Hey. just stay away from me.

660
01:04:53.590 --> 01:04:55.230
I don't want to hurt you. all right?

661
01:04:55.460 --> 01:04:56.220
Don't move.

662
01:04:56.860 --> 01:04:58.360
I just want to talk to you.

663
01:04:58.580 --> 01:04:59.510
Well. I don't.

664
01:04:59.810 --> 01:05:00.510
Stay back.

665
01:05:01.510 --> 01:05:02.770
I said don't move!

666
01:05:03.390 --> 01:05:04.250
Don't move!

667
01:06:23.380 --> 01:06:25.100
This one is the real one.

668
01:06:26.790 --> 01:06:28.690
If I wanted to kill you. I'd do it right now.

669
01:06:28.770 --> 01:06:29.970
Now put your hands down.

670
01:06:35.150 --> 01:06:37.210
Ian. I know you've been looking for your parents.

671
01:06:39.650 --> 01:06:42.250
You know. I've been looking for you too. son.

672
01:06:43.100 --> 01:06:43.910
You?

673
01:06:45.570 --> 01:06:47.410
I don't believe a fucking word you're saying.

674
01:07:08.870 --> 01:07:10.090
We're a product. Ian.

675
01:07:10.890 --> 01:07:11.880
A creation.

676
01:07:12.560 --> 01:07:15.080
The result of a secret program that started in the 50s.

677
01:07:15.190 --> 01:07:16.300
after World War II.

678
01:07:17.200 --> 01:07:19.020
There were a group of volunteers.

679
01:07:19.350 --> 01:07:20.710
your mom and I among them.

680
01:07:21.270 --> 01:07:23.870
Kaminsky injected us with a compound of his own creation.

681
01:07:25.600 --> 01:07:26.680
The formula.

682
01:07:27.310 --> 01:07:28.070
Yes.

683
01:07:28.900 --> 01:07:30.180
And thanks to the formula.

684
01:07:30.600 --> 01:07:33.460
we all suddenly developed certain extrasensory abilities.

685
01:07:35.480 --> 01:07:37.360
Ian. we're spies with mind control.

686
01:07:39.230 --> 01:07:42.450
But when the Cold War was over. governments didn't know what to do with us.

687
01:07:42.770 --> 01:07:45.310
I guess they feared we would organize. or...

688
01:07:46.130 --> 01:07:48.110
or ally ourselves with the enemy.

689
01:07:51.980 --> 01:07:53.860
So they decided to exterminate us all.

690
01:07:55.250 --> 01:07:57.130
They called it the disinfection.

691
01:07:59.560 --> 01:08:01.700
They hunted us down one by one.

692
01:08:02.680 --> 01:08:03.700
Like rabbits.

693
01:08:05.560 --> 01:08:07.020
We didn't stand a chance.

694
01:08:16.190 --> 01:08:17.750
Until the arrival of the Mule.

695
01:08:19.620 --> 01:08:21.900
He's the last and most powerful perceiver.

696
01:08:23.520 --> 01:08:25.000
The perfect weapon.

697
01:08:29.180 --> 01:08:32.820
When they went after him. the Mule fought back.

698
01:08:43.920 --> 01:08:45.750
A few days before the disinfection.

699
01:08:46.050 --> 01:08:49.820
they found signs of a new ability that made the agency tremble with fear.

700
01:08:52.270 --> 01:08:53.710
The third power.

701
01:08:54.870 --> 01:08:56.070
Total subjugation.

702
01:08:57.290 --> 01:08:58.610
Breaking anybody's will.

703
01:08:59.570 --> 01:09:00.940
Making them do what you want.

704
01:09:01.550 --> 01:09:02.420
How you want it.

705
01:09:02.720 --> 01:09:03.540
When you want it.

706
01:09:04.210 --> 01:09:05.150
Where you want it.

707
01:09:07.060 --> 01:09:08.280
Like a puppet master.

708
01:09:11.470 --> 01:09:14.610
He gathered all the survivors and created the awareness.

709
01:09:15.230 --> 01:09:17.970
He taught us how to go unnoticed without using our powers.

710
01:09:22.130 --> 01:09:23.470
Why is he called the Mule?

711
01:09:24.220 --> 01:09:25.860
Because perceivers are like mules.

712
01:09:26.670 --> 01:09:27.590
They're sterile.

713
01:09:28.420 --> 01:09:30.840
Governments made absolutely sure we couldn't have children.

714
01:09:31.360 --> 01:09:34.220
But I thought my parents were also perceivers.

715
01:09:35.080 --> 01:09:36.820
Yes. and that's the miracle in all this.

716
01:09:37.830 --> 01:09:38.890
It was impossible.

717
01:09:39.440 --> 01:09:41.260
Your mother and I. we had been together for years.

718
01:09:42.380 --> 01:09:46.020
And all of a sudden. one day she realized she was pregnant with you.

719
01:09:47.470 --> 01:09:48.390
And you were.

720
01:09:49.540 --> 01:09:51.520
The first natural born perceiver.

721
01:09:51.910 --> 01:09:53.000
What the fuck?

722
01:10:10.970 --> 01:10:12.540
Get up behind me and go to the roof.

723
01:10:12.630 --> 01:10:14.100
I'll cover you. Okay

724
01:10:14.820 --> 01:10:16.640
I don't believe a single word

725
01:10:17.210 --> 01:10:18.230
Stop lying to me.

726
01:10:18.810 --> 01:10:20.430
Tell me. where is my mother?

727
01:10:22.280 --> 01:10:23.860
Listen to me. I don't like to argue.

728
01:10:24.220 --> 01:10:25.240
Go back to Spain.

729
01:10:25.450 --> 01:10:26.750
I have a house just outside Madrid.

730
01:10:26.810 --> 01:10:27.640
She knows where.

731
01:10:31.410 --> 01:10:32.290
All right.

732
01:10:33.870 --> 01:10:34.750
Trust us.

733
01:11:32.910 --> 01:11:33.810
Wait here

734
01:13:16.910 --> 01:13:18.530
No emergency stairs!

735
01:13:19.110 --> 01:13:19.890
There!

736
01:13:30.910 --> 01:13:31.730
Ian!

737
01:13:32.130 --> 01:13:33.180
There's no time!

738
01:13:34.380 --> 01:13:35.380
Esther

739
01:13:47.810 --> 01:13:49.240
Come down. Ian

740
01:14:43.860 --> 01:14:45.180
I'll make you regret this!

741
01:14:45.280 --> 01:14:46.180
You'll see!

742
01:14:47.220 --> 01:14:48.140
All of you!

743
01:15:04.050 --> 01:15:05.810
Your plan almost worked. huh?

744
01:15:06.330 --> 01:15:07.320
Had me

745
01:15:07.680 --> 01:15:09.040
find the kid so you could

746
01:15:09.470 --> 01:15:10.490
capture us both.

747
01:15:10.890 --> 01:15:12.440
This is called strategy.

748
01:15:13.810 --> 01:15:15.450
You may have powers.

749
01:15:16.200 --> 01:15:17.690
but we have the brains

750
01:15:18.220 --> 01:15:19.470
and the muscle.

751
01:15:20.270 --> 01:15:22.360
And we'll soon know whether you're the mule

752
01:15:22.720 --> 01:15:24.460
or if he's just a legend.

753
01:15:25.190 --> 01:15:26.970
Then you'll tell us where the kid is.

754
01:15:27.350 --> 01:15:30.100
And if I don't. what are you gonna do?

755
01:15:30.650 --> 01:15:31.990
Kill me?

756
01:15:32.740 --> 01:15:33.570
No.

757
01:15:34.910 --> 01:15:35.770
Not yet.

758
01:15:37.560 --> 01:15:39.640
As soon as I manage to find the formula.

759
01:15:39.710 --> 01:15:41.170
I'll take your powers away.

760
01:15:41.800 --> 01:15:42.620
And then.

761
01:15:43.470 --> 01:15:45.670
you're gonna start begging me to kill you.

762
01:15:47.370 --> 01:15:48.830
You fucking bitch.

763
01:15:49.350 --> 01:15:51.690
I guess sterilizing me wasn't enough for you.

764
01:15:52.670 --> 01:15:54.430
You can initiate the tests.

765
01:15:55.230 --> 01:15:56.970
Listen to yourself. Adriana.

766
01:15:57.040 --> 01:15:58.540
You sound just like Kaminsky.

767
01:15:58.880 --> 01:16:00.280
I want that formula.

768
01:16:33.100 --> 01:16:34.750
Stop this insanity.

769
01:16:35.130 --> 01:16:35.910
Now!

770
01:16:37.290 --> 01:16:38.670
That is a direct order.

771
01:16:44.040 --> 01:16:44.780
Adriana.

772
01:16:45.780 --> 01:16:47.640
it's no good till he's dead.

773
01:17:13.200 --> 01:17:14.200
Doctor.

774
01:17:16.210 --> 01:17:17.550
I have bad news.

775
01:17:18.760 --> 01:17:19.720
The formula.

776
01:17:21.710 --> 01:17:24.080
It's so diluted in his body that

777
01:17:24.910 --> 01:17:26.910
it's impossible to synthesize it.

778
01:17:28.340 --> 01:17:29.420
I'm thirsty.

779
01:17:30.660 --> 01:17:31.780
Can I have some water?

780
01:17:33.350 --> 01:17:34.450
It's very hot in here.

781
01:17:34.560 --> 01:17:35.520
you bastards.

782
01:17:49.800 --> 01:17:50.880
It's over.

783
01:17:53.610 --> 01:17:54.830
We're done for.

784
01:17:56.040 --> 01:17:58.330
The formula died with Kaminsky.

785
01:18:03.380 --> 01:18:05.120
The boy is our only hope.

786
01:18:33.510 --> 01:18:34.970
Just keep your mouth open.

787
01:19:26.720 --> 01:19:27.940
What are you doing. doctor?

788
01:19:29.240 --> 01:19:31.410
Return the robot to its initial position.

789
01:19:31.650 --> 01:19:32.930
Do it right now.

790
01:19:33.220 --> 01:19:34.660
I can't control it

791
01:19:34.870 --> 01:19:36.950
Get your hands off the control!

792
01:19:38.390 --> 01:19:40.460
Get your hands off the control!

793
01:21:45.070 --> 01:21:45.850
This way.

794
01:21:54.040 --> 01:21:55.940
She likes when I sing to her.

795
01:22:34.700 --> 01:22:35.350
Mom?

796
01:22:36.860 --> 01:22:38.820
I know you've pictured this moment

797
01:22:38.840 --> 01:22:40.040
over and over again.

798
01:22:43.070 --> 01:22:44.010
I'm sorry. son.

799
01:22:45.480 --> 01:22:47.200
It's not what you thought it would be.

800
01:22:49.170 --> 01:22:50.910
But your mother isn't gone. Ian.

801
01:22:51.260 --> 01:22:52.730
She's still in there somewhere.

802
01:22:54.210 --> 01:22:56.570
And in there. you can be together again.

803
01:23:01.930 --> 01:23:02.820
Hey. Mom.

804
01:23:45.470 --> 01:23:46.910
Ian. look at your mother.

805
01:23:48.930 --> 01:23:49.590
This

806
01:23:50.630 --> 01:23:52.570
is what they do to our people.

807
01:23:53.720 --> 01:23:55.280
Right before she was captured.

808
01:23:55.790 --> 01:23:57.990
Ursula managed to insert a memory in your mind.

809
01:23:59.150 --> 01:24:00.450
This memory right here.

810
01:24:00.990 --> 01:24:02.670
She knew that without the formula.

811
01:24:03.010 --> 01:24:05.230
they wouldn't be able to make new perceivers.

812
01:24:05.920 --> 01:24:08.640
She destroyed the only copy that Kaminsky had.

813
01:24:09.940 --> 01:24:11.040
And the original?

814
01:24:11.410 --> 01:24:13.010
She encrypted into your memory.

815
01:24:14.670 --> 01:24:15.380
Ian.

816
01:24:18.080 --> 01:24:19.460
With that formula.

817
01:24:20.190 --> 01:24:22.250
we would be able to make new perceivers.

818
01:24:22.670 --> 01:24:24.130
And finally get rid of the agency

819
01:24:24.160 --> 01:24:25.560
which caused so much pain.

820
01:24:26.260 --> 01:24:27.030
To you.

821
01:24:27.900 --> 01:24:28.860
to me.

822
01:24:29.400 --> 01:24:31.070
and to your mother.

823
01:24:36.050 --> 01:24:36.760
Ian.

824
01:24:41.480 --> 01:24:42.970
You can't come and get them yourself.

825
01:24:43.120 --> 01:24:44.750
There's no time for that. son.

826
01:24:44.810 --> 01:24:45.730
Hand them over.

827
01:24:46.820 --> 01:24:48.420
She didn't want anyone to see them.

828
01:24:53.320 --> 01:24:54.320
Only me

829
01:25:00.240 --> 01:25:01.820
Give me the formula. damn it!

830
01:25:02.060 --> 01:25:04.450
It's the only way I can protect you from the agency.

831
01:25:08.380 --> 01:25:09.820
Stop! Stop! Stop!

832
01:25:14.300 --> 01:25:15.300
Stop!

833
01:25:17.810 --> 01:25:19.160
Stop it! You are hurt her.

834
01:25:46.550 --> 01:25:47.550
Don't worry

835
01:25:49.600 --> 01:25:50.760
about a thing.

836
01:25:54.520 --> 01:25:55.960
Every little thing

837
01:25:58.080 --> 01:25:59.980
is gonna be alright.

838
01:27:00.890 --> 01:27:02.570
Step away from the boy!

839
01:27:41.690 --> 01:27:42.690
There it is

840
01:27:44.250 --> 01:27:45.930
It's the third power.

841
01:27:46.320 --> 01:27:47.320
I knew it.

842
01:28:01.410 --> 01:28:02.410
Ian

843
01:28:03.490 --> 01:28:04.490
Ian

844
01:28:11.400 --> 01:28:12.840
I can't move.

845
01:28:17.170 --> 01:28:18.170
Ian

846
01:28:26.260 --> 01:28:27.410
What are you doing?

847
01:29:06.230 --> 01:29:08.050
Ian. don't move

848
01:29:13.220 --> 01:29:14.220
Stop. Ian.

849
01:29:14.890 --> 01:29:16.180
Don't make me do it.

850
01:29:28.940 --> 01:29:29.940
Open fire!

851
01:29:31.600 --> 01:29:32.600
Shoot now!

852
01:29:32.810 --> 01:29:34.350
That's a direct order!

853
01:29:47.100 --> 01:29:48.080
I finally saw it.

854
01:29:48.330 --> 01:29:49.680
No. Ian. stop.

855
01:29:50.060 --> 01:29:52.460
What did you see? Is she alive?

856
01:29:52.540 --> 01:29:53.580
Do it. son.

857
01:29:54.080 --> 01:29:55.670
She is the one to blame.

858
01:29:58.130 --> 01:29:59.990
We lost her mother many years ago.

859
01:30:00.180 --> 01:30:02.380
Whatever you saw. he's the one that did it!

860
01:30:02.650 --> 01:30:03.620
You're lying!

861
01:30:05.170 --> 01:30:06.400
You are gonna pay

862
01:30:06.430 --> 01:30:07.650
for what you did to my mother.

863
01:30:08.200 --> 01:30:10.180
Opening up her head like a rat.

864
01:30:10.730 --> 01:30:11.570
You're sick.

865
01:30:12.930 --> 01:30:13.910
No. no.

866
01:30:14.950 --> 01:30:15.910
Do it.

867
01:30:16.500 --> 01:30:17.360
Come on. now!

868
01:30:17.430 --> 01:30:18.080
Ian.

869
01:30:21.920 --> 01:30:22.650
You.

870
01:30:24.730 --> 01:30:25.930
You're on their side?

871
01:30:28.310 --> 01:30:29.270
Don't do it. Ian.

872
01:30:29.470 --> 01:30:30.330
You have to stop.

873
01:30:31.010 --> 01:30:32.110
Stay out of this.

874
01:30:33.820 --> 01:30:34.420
Ian.

875
01:30:36.040 --> 01:30:38.020
He's manipulating you. Look at him!

876
01:30:38.230 --> 01:30:39.880
He's treating you like a puppet!

877
01:30:40.110 --> 01:30:41.540
And he's treating you like a child.

878
01:30:41.610 --> 01:30:42.110
Shut up!

879
01:30:42.960 --> 01:30:43.840
Leave me alone!

880
01:30:56.240 --> 01:30:57.240
Do it.

881
01:30:57.600 --> 01:30:58.860
Make him do it as well.

882
01:30:59.080 --> 01:31:00.160
Don't do it.

883
01:31:00.320 --> 01:31:01.940
You'll regret it for the rest of your life.

884
01:31:02.730 --> 01:31:03.440
Look at them.

885
01:31:11.770 --> 01:31:13.450
Look at their eyes. They're terrified.

886
01:31:18.020 --> 01:31:18.860
Go now.

887
01:31:22.180 --> 01:31:23.250
The Agency.

888
01:31:25.780 --> 01:31:27.500
They're the ones who tortured my mother

889
01:31:27.530 --> 01:31:29.220
until she was nothing but a vegetable.

890
01:31:31.000 --> 01:31:33.000
All because of the goddamn formula.

891
01:31:34.220 --> 01:31:35.440
And to eliminate us.

892
01:31:39.420 --> 01:31:40.080
Ian.

893
01:31:41.430 --> 01:31:42.350
Look around.

894
01:31:42.440 --> 01:31:43.920
Is this really what you want?

895
01:31:44.440 --> 01:31:46.920
Don't let him control you like he always has.

896
01:31:47.410 --> 01:31:48.890
Look at the life you've had.

897
01:31:49.150 --> 01:31:50.450
No family. no friends.

898
01:31:51.050 --> 01:31:53.050
Now you actually have a real chance.

899
01:31:53.550 --> 01:31:54.870
Finally be part of something.

900
01:31:55.650 --> 01:31:56.710
Don't listen to him.

901
01:31:57.130 --> 01:31:57.990
He's a drunk.

902
01:31:58.590 --> 01:31:59.610
Listen to your father.

903
01:32:00.140 --> 01:32:01.120
Father?

904
01:32:02.150 --> 01:32:04.070
Your father is the one who loves you.

905
01:32:04.250 --> 01:32:05.650
The father always puts you first.

906
01:32:05.710 --> 01:32:07.630
He sacrifices everything for you.

907
01:32:17.680 --> 01:32:18.960
What have you done?

908
01:32:32.190 --> 01:32:33.610
Ian!

909
01:32:47.020 --> 01:32:48.730
No.

910
01:32:49.050 --> 01:32:51.250
No.

911
01:32:52.920 --> 01:32:53.920
If I go in

912
01:32:54.900 --> 01:32:56.400
You're not gonna make it.

913
01:32:57.440 --> 01:32:58.090
No.

914
01:32:58.800 --> 01:32:59.300
No.

915
01:32:59.530 --> 01:33:01.790
Go in. Please go in there. Ian.

916
01:33:02.040 --> 01:33:04.480
And see it for. for yourself.

917
01:33:21.250 --> 01:33:23.090
I know you're not like the others.

918
01:33:23.860 --> 01:33:25.460
I can feel all your suffering.

919
01:33:25.710 --> 01:33:26.730
Let go of me. please.

920
01:33:26.890 --> 01:33:27.780
He's here.

921
01:33:28.490 --> 01:33:30.110
He's coming to take him away.

922
01:33:30.660 --> 01:33:32.830
Don't let them hurt him. I'm begging you.

923
01:33:33.810 --> 01:33:35.110
You have to take him.

924
01:33:35.350 --> 01:33:36.510
Promise me you'll do it.

925
01:33:37.030 --> 01:33:37.670
Please.

926
01:33:38.460 --> 01:33:40.450
The boy deserves to have a future.

927
01:33:47.450 --> 01:33:48.890
I'm gonna go see what the issue is.

928
01:34:02.620 --> 01:34:04.060
Please forgive me.

929
01:34:12.320 --> 01:34:15.910
Dad. forgive me. forgive me.

930
01:34:16.010 --> 01:34:17.420
Stop that.

931
01:34:20.160 --> 01:34:20.680
Hey.

932
01:34:22.610 --> 01:34:24.930
I'm the one who should be apologizing.

933
01:34:26.430 --> 01:34:27.950
You gave up your entire life

934
01:34:31.260 --> 01:34:32.800
just so I could have one.

935
01:34:35.430 --> 01:34:37.770
I never should have kept anything from you.

936
01:34:39.480 --> 01:34:40.420
I was wrong.

937
01:34:42.820 --> 01:34:43.860
But you...

938
01:34:44.760 --> 01:34:45.940
You can do it.

939
01:34:45.960 --> 01:34:47.780
You have to find your own path.

940
01:34:55.850 --> 01:34:56.970
Are they coming today?

941
01:34:57.970 --> 01:34:59.190
The trick is to be patient

942
01:34:59.520 --> 01:35:01.380
like when we play hide and seek.

943
01:35:03.070 --> 01:35:04.690
What if there aren't any more fish?

944
01:35:05.090 --> 01:35:05.720
Ian.

945
01:35:07.100 --> 01:35:08.980
How could there not be any more fish?

946
01:35:09.410 --> 01:35:10.670
Like how big the ocean is.

947
01:35:10.730 --> 01:35:11.600
Can you see the end?

948
01:35:11.630 --> 01:35:13.250
Yes. the line is the end.

949
01:35:15.320 --> 01:35:16.280
Listen to me.

950
01:35:16.690 --> 01:35:18.090
Just because you can't see it

951
01:35:18.190 --> 01:35:20.050
doesn't mean it's not there.

952
01:35:21.050 --> 01:35:22.380
Beyond that line.

953
01:35:22.770 --> 01:35:24.050
there's so much more.

954
01:35:24.950 --> 01:35:26.200
So much more.

955
01:35:28.290 --> 01:35:29.710
So don't ever give up.

956
01:35:29.960 --> 01:35:30.860
You hear me?

957
01:35:31.720 --> 01:35:34.220
The best fish. who gets them?

958
01:35:34.530 --> 01:35:36.090
The person who always has hope.

959
01:35:36.160 --> 01:35:37.100
Yeah.

960
01:36:10.750 --> 01:36:11.750
Dad? 

961
01:36:13.810 --> 01:36:14.590
Dad?

962
01:36:15.920 --> 01:36:16.750
Dad?

963
01:36:18.570 --> 01:36:19.350
No.

964
01:37:08.860 --> 01:37:09.860
Ian

965
01:37:42.260 --> 01:37:44.250
Stop right there. Don't move.

966
01:38:05.190 --> 01:38:06.570
You're strong. son.

967
01:38:07.730 --> 01:38:09.390
But you can't control it yet.

968
01:38:09.730 --> 01:38:11.010
Your eyes give it away.

969
01:38:19.090 --> 01:38:19.920
Calm down.

970
01:38:26.330 --> 01:38:27.170
Stay back.

971
01:41:22.290 --> 01:41:24.610
You take one more step and I'll shoot her right in the head.

972
01:41:31.410 --> 01:41:32.920
Please do what he says. Ian.

973
01:41:34.420 --> 01:41:35.980
You took advantage of me.

974
01:41:37.230 --> 01:41:38.450
Like everyone else!

975
01:41:40.380 --> 01:41:41.980
All you want is the formula.

976
01:41:42.850 --> 01:41:43.820
That's about it.

977
01:41:44.520 --> 01:41:45.970
Let me see it in your mind. son.

978
01:41:46.360 --> 01:41:48.080
And then I'll leave. without hurting her.

979
01:41:48.870 --> 01:41:50.550
She's got nothing to do with this.

980
01:41:50.910 --> 01:41:51.610
She?

981
01:41:52.780 --> 01:41:53.980
Don't listen to him!

982
01:41:54.440 --> 01:41:56.460
Whoever she is. she's a projection.

983
01:41:56.780 --> 01:41:58.530
They put a loop inside your head.

984
01:42:00.240 --> 01:42:01.300
What are you saying?

985
01:42:01.770 --> 01:42:03.030
I can't see her.

986
01:42:03.210 --> 01:42:04.570
No one else can see her.

987
01:42:04.700 --> 01:42:05.600
Only you can.

988
01:42:05.980 --> 01:42:07.060
She's lying to you.

989
01:42:07.170 --> 01:42:08.400
She's messing with your head.

990
01:42:08.800 --> 01:42:10.580
She's the one who told you that's impossible.

991
01:42:11.030 --> 01:42:12.620
Weigh your options carefully.

992
01:42:12.900 --> 01:42:14.360
Whatever you decide.

993
01:42:15.990 --> 01:42:17.500
there's no going back from that.

994
01:42:21.030 --> 01:42:22.150
Shall I pull the trigger

995
01:42:22.180 --> 01:42:23.700
so you can see if the girl's real?

996
01:42:24.410 --> 01:42:25.910
This is between you and me.

997
01:42:26.600 --> 01:42:28.260
Ian. try to remember.

998
01:42:28.670 --> 01:42:31.240
He must have put that loop in your head at some point.

999
01:43:42.290 --> 01:43:43.040
Ian!

1000
01:43:44.030 --> 01:43:45.060
Put the gun down.

1001
01:43:45.440 --> 01:43:46.790
Please. I don't want to die.

1002
01:43:47.790 --> 01:43:48.790
Just shut up!

1003
01:43:49.600 --> 01:43:51.060
I don't want to listen to you.

1004
01:43:52.490 --> 01:43:53.270
Look at me.

1005
01:43:54.570 --> 01:43:56.270
I know you feel the same way I do.

1006
01:43:57.870 --> 01:43:58.760
Isn't that real?

1007
01:43:59.120 --> 01:44:00.380
No. you're not real.

1008
01:44:01.600 --> 01:44:02.700
You're just in my head.

1009
01:44:02.830 --> 01:44:03.870
Are you sure about that?

1010
01:44:04.900 --> 01:44:06.620
That's a big bet you're taking. son.

1011
01:44:27.280 --> 01:44:28.360
I am not

1012
01:44:29.510 --> 01:44:30.410
your son.

1013
01:45:38.590 --> 01:45:40.010
This was only the beginning.

1014
01:45:42.490 --> 01:45:44.170
I've already lost way too much.

1015
01:45:47.930 --> 01:45:50.260
The only people who ever cared about me.

1016
01:45:57.120 --> 01:45:59.160
And 18 years I want to get back.

1017
01:46:09.050 --> 01:46:10.850
We need the formula. Ian.

1018
01:46:11.700 --> 01:46:13.220
We need you on our side.

1019
01:46:14.260 --> 01:46:16.800
This war will seal the fate of many people.

1020
01:46:17.990 --> 01:46:18.900
Innocent people.

1021
01:46:20.480 --> 01:46:22.160
You can't stay out of it.

1022
01:46:29.210 --> 01:46:31.490
You have to decide which side you're on.

1023
01:46:36.780 --> 01:46:38.000
No man's land.

1024
01:46:40.260 --> 01:46:41.660
Heard of it. doctor?

1025
01:46:50.860 --> 01:46:53.180
You didn't have to do this.

1026
01:46:53.610 --> 01:46:55.070
You could have just asked me.

1027
01:47:02.260 --> 01:47:03.420
I'll think about it.

1028
01:47:20.790 --> 01:47:22.890
My dad gave that to me on my birthday.

1029
01:47:24.210 --> 01:47:25.730
So why don't you open it. then?

1030
01:47:37.070 --> 01:47:38.680
The majesty of the ocean.

1031
01:47:48.260 --> 01:47:49.460
I love you. dad.

1032
01:48:27.260 --> 01:48:28.460
We should have killed him.

1033
01:48:28.930 --> 01:48:30.130
He's a loose cannon now.

1034
01:48:30.940 --> 01:48:32.180
You're not wrong.

1035
01:48:32.690 --> 01:48:33.990
He's out of Vicente's control.

1036
01:48:34.840 --> 01:48:36.760
He's out of the perceiver's control. too.

1037
01:48:39.700 --> 01:48:41.100
But he trusts me.

1038
01:48:43.750 --> 01:48:45.570
Still thinking you can recruit him?

1039
01:48:46.770 --> 01:48:48.050
I believe so.

1040
01:48:48.500 --> 01:48:49.120
Yes.

1041
01:48:50.950 --> 01:48:52.930
What if you don't succeed?

1042
01:48:54.470 --> 01:48:56.160
If I don't succeed...

1043
01:48:58.100 --> 01:49:00.340
Then I'll eliminate him myself.

1044
01:49:06.780 --> 01:49:10.800

